<h3>Astrofish.net</h3>

<p>&quot;Twenty lines of code, and it changed my life,&quot; Kramer Wetzel told me after I wrote a script to automate the publishing of his horoscopes.</p>

<p>Kramer writes his astrology column weeks in advance, but to publish his horoscopes on Thursday mornings, he had to make sure a computer with Internet access was available on his travels.</p>

<p>He asked me whether it was possible to automate publication. I said it was.</p>

<p>Kramer's file system, luckily, was based on dates, and it allowed me to parse the file names through PHP and compare them with a timestamp.</p>

<p>The script reads in a list of publishable file names, determines which one of those files falls within that particular publishing week and displays it -- without Kramer having to step near a computer.</p>
